valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Unity's  actions</span><hr size=1> The actions of Unity must be answered.  It is irrelevant what occurs on other servers because we reside on Prexus.   <br>
<br>
The consensus of Prexus was to abide by the calendar, which included Unity.  Until a consensus has been made to change it, if the consensus saw the need for change.   <br>
<br>
How is what Unity did different from the 3 druids that took the gorgons in Fear that night?  It is no different in principle.<br>
<br>
What happens to guilds that blatantly violate the calendar?  Their calendar ID is revoked.<br>
<br>
In response to their action, Unity must live with the consequences.  Whether their action spurs change is irrelevant.<br>
<br>
The following must occur:<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Unity must be blacklisted on this server.  That means no buffings, rezzes, ports, invitations to groups, no   trading with a Unity member or any other form of assistance<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Unity’s scheduled raids must be FCFS.   A conglomeration of small and medium sized guilds will band together to usurp all planned Unity raids. There calendar will be posted on this thread on a later date.<br>
<br>
<br>
This will change when Unity takes back their action, admits their wrongdoing and makes amends to Souls of Mir and all of Prexus that they were disrespectful to.<br>
<br>
As far as Unity assuming they have power, they only have power because we give it to them.  A united front by every other player on this server will put the power where it belongs, with each one of us that live on the Prexus server in Norrath.<br>
<br>
I am also calling for a meeting to achieve a consensus on changes to the calendar.  It will occur on Monday evening 7pm Central Standard Time.   A chat room will be enabled and a password established. Once you have posted on the message board you will be contacted in game with the password.  Those that choose to attend should post at this link. <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.showMessage?topicID=8800.topic">pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus...8800.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->   It is recommended that guilds send two representatives and have a discussion with their guild membership so they can represent their guild.   Ideally this should be guild leader and one officer. A consensus Monday night before the end of the meeting. The name of the chat room will be Prexus Consensus.  I have faith a reasonable consensus will be reached.  Rules for discussion will be   established. Those not following the rules will be removed from the chat room.<br>
<br>
This will be posted on every guild message board.  There are many on the calendar that does not participate on the Prexus.com message board.  As such the discussion on the message board, has not been representative of Prexus.<br>
